### snprintf - Writes formatted output to a string buffer with size limit

Source: https://en.cppreference.com/w/c/io/fprintf

The `snprintf` function formats data and writes it into a character string buffer, ensuring that it does not write more than `bufsz - 1` characters. A null terminator is always appended if `bufsz` is not zero. 

```APIDOC
## snprintf

### Description
Formats data and writes it to a character string buffer, ensuring that at most `bufsz - 1` characters are written. The resulting string is null-terminated if `bufsz > 0`.

### Method
N/A (C standard library function)

### Endpoint
N/A

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
