### Request Example
```c
char buffer[20];
int written = snprintf(buffer, sizeof(buffer), "Short string: %s", "This is too long to fit");
printf("Characters written: %d\n", written);
printf("Buffer content: %s\n", buffer);
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
Returns the number of characters that would have been written if `bufsz` were large enough (excluding the null terminator). If `bufsz` is zero, nothing is written, but the return value is still calculated.

