### Determine Buffer Size with snprintf

Source: https://en.cppreference.com/w/c/io/fprintf

This snippet demonstrates how to use `snprintf` with a NULL buffer and zero size to determine the required buffer size for a formatted string. It's a safe way to pre-allocate memory before actual output.

```cpp
const char fmt[] = "sqrt(2) = %f";
int sz = snprintf(NULL, 0, fmt, sqrt(2));
char buf[sz + 1]; // note +1 for terminating null byte
snprintf(buf, sizeof buf, fmt, sqrt(2));
